application.resources.gates

Class andController

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.resources.gates.gateObject
      • application.resources.gates.andController
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.fxml.Initializable

    public class andController
extends gateObject
implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
    The andController class represents a AND gate controller extending gateObject. It contains functionality specific to NAND gate behavior in a circuit simulation. Generators in Sandbox and Levels create instances of AND gates. This class then controls the AND logic cases of those gates, while also handling dragging and dropping.
    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    sandboxController

      • checktype

        public void checktype()
        Checks the type of the AND gate based on its inputs. If both inputs are connected and active, the output is set to true. If either input is not connected or inactive, the output is set to false. Updates the output state and calls Rectangle on the connected node.
